<H3> <TI>     BUM Impact Drilling Machine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94UM0165F Moscow VOYENNYY VESTNIK in Russian No 10, Oct 93 
Special Edition (signed to press 20 Aug 93) p 21 </F>

<F P=103> 94UM0165F </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow VOYENNYY VESTNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Engineer V. Konyakhin] </F>
  [Text] The machine is designed for drilling boreholes in 
rock and wells in frozen and unfrozen ground when doing engineer 
work. 
  It consists of a KamAZ-4310 base chassis and operating 
equipment, which includes a distribution box with an oil pump 
and compressor, a traversing platform on which rifle equipment 
is installed, and the drilling mechanism with the working 
instrument. 
  The machine used the design of a modern impact-rotary method 
of breaking up rock. The impact frequency is 83-94 Hz. 
  The impact drilling machine can be successfully used in 
fortification of troop positions by the explosive method in 
conditions of frozen ground and in rock. 


